						TAMIL WORD SMOOTHER 1.0
						-------------------------

TAMIL WORD SMOOTHER :
---------------------

The task of smooting of words that are  generated. If a word is ending with a vowel [a,A,i,I,eV,E,r,y,lYY] and its next token is starting with constants like k,c,t,w,p the previous word should also end with the strating constant of the next word.

Requirements:
------------
Operating System		:    LINUX/UNIX system

Compiler/Interpreter/Librarie(s):    Perl and SSF API's

For installation on Linux, please refer to the file INSTALL.


Directory Structure:
--------------------

telwordgen
     |
     |---API (SSF API's)
     |
     |---tests (contains the referenece input and output)
     |
     |---README (How to run/use the module)
     |
     |---INSTALL  (How to install in sampark directory structure)
     |
     |---ChangeLog (version inforamation)
     |
     |---Makefile (first level make file for copying the module source in sampark system)
     |
     |---Makefile.stage2 (2nd level make file for actual installation/copying in the bin and data_bin directory)
     |
     |---word_smt.pl (main file of word smoother)




How to Use??
------------

1. perl $setu/bin/tl/word_smt.pl --path=$setu/bin/tl/word_smt.pl --input=$setu/bin/tl/word_smt/tests/word_smt.rin

   *sample input and output files are provided in the tests dir namely word_smt.rin word_smt.rout

2. perl $setu/bin/tl/word_smt/word_smt.pl --help
   for display the help


